{"title":"In The Drops: ThinkRider X2Max Smart Trainer, Muc-Off Foam Sprayer, GripGrab FastStream gloves and James Blake","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/thinkrider-x2max-smart-trainer","date":1773426509000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/thinkrider-x2max-smart-trainer\">In The Drops: ThinkRider X2Max Smart Trainer, Muc-Off Foam Sprayer, GripGrab FastStream gloves and James Blake</a></p>\n\n<p>It might be Friday the 13th, but I promise you nothing cursed – or Lindsey Lohan related – in this week’s In The Drops.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start then by rounding up this week’s<em> </em>stories with the tech headlines. Cannondale stole the limelight earlier this week by unveiling <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cannondale-caad14\">the 14th generation of its iconic CAAD</a>. We had photographer Xavier Pereyron photographing<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-bikes-2026\"> the pros’ best bikes from Strade Bianche</a> last weekend. If you’ve got a moment, take a look at <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-strade-bianche-colnago-y1rs\">Tadej Pogačar’s raw carbon Colnago Y1Rs</a>. He’s made some sneaky adjustments to that aero bike to keep it as light as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Elsewhere on the pro calendar, Paris-Nice and Tirreno-Adriatico come to their conclusions this weekend. <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gc-paris-nice-tirreno-adriatico-2026\">We anticipated some of the storylines</a> to follow, while Robyn cast an eager eye on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paul-seixas-great-expectations\">the growth of Paul Seixas</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/picnic-postnl\">the decline of Picnic-PostNL</a>. Seriously, the Dutch team are in real dire straits at the moment.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, let’s shift our focus and head into the drops.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            \r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mattias-skjelmose-interview\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-150x150.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-45x45.jpg 45w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-75x75.jpg 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-350x350.jpg 350w\" alt=\"Cyclist-Mag-Skjelly-Images-Lidl-Trek-Hardycc-12-150x150.jpg\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>'I see myself as a winner': Mattias Skjelmose Q&amp;A</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ineos-grenadiers-superteam\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-150x150.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-45x45.jpg 45w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-75x75.jpg 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-350x350.jpg 350w\" alt=\"20260310PNC0158_A.S.O.-Billy-Ceusters-crop-150x150.jpg\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>Can Ineos Grenadiers return to superteam status?</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-bikes-2026\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-150x150.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-45x45.jpg 45w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-75x75.jpg 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-350x350.jpg 350w\" alt=\"Cyclist-Mens-Bikes-07-mars-2026-22-150x150.jpg\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>Strade Bianche bikes 2026: Not as interesting as they once were but still nice to look at</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cannondale-caad14\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-150x150.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-45x45.jpg 45w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-75x75.jpg 75w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-350x350.jpg 350w\" alt=\"C26_CAAD14_1_RAW_Beauty_0001-150x150.jpg\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>Stunning new CAAD14 goes back to Cannondale's alloy bike roots</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>ThinkRider X2Max Smart Trainer</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smaret-trainer-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AliExpress has been expanding its cycling repertoire in recent years. Just take a look at Instagram and you’ll see influencers singing the praises of their AliExpress finds. I mean, it was only last September that Harry Hudson won a World Championships gold medal on board the 6.8kg QuickPro AR: One, which similarly comes directly from China.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Components and clothing aren’t the only cycling goodies available on AliExpress these days. No, smart trainers have also reached the platform. With that, let me introduce you to the ThinkRider X2Max Smart Trainer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This £250 smart trainer works just like any other. Just slide your cassette on and connect the trainer to your preferred training app (Zwift, Rouvy, Wahoo etc). The X2Max has an integrated power meter that sends wattage and cadence data for every workout, and its accuracy is in line with most big-name brands, with the X2Max claiming power meter reading with around 2% margin of error.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-970x647.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-970x646.png 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-300x200.png 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-768x512.png 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-2048x1365.png 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-750x500.png 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-1140x760.png 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-465x310.png 465w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-620x413.png 620w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/smart-trainer-2-350x233.png 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In terms of other specifications, the X2Max has a maximum 2000W output and can simulate gradients of up to 18%. The trainer is compatible with Shimano 8- to 12-speed cassettes and SRAM 8- to 11-speed cassettes. An XDR free-hub is needed to attach a SRAM 12-speed cassette, but it is possible. The trainer also comes equipped with a thru axle and quick-release adapters to help mount your bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.aliexpress.com/item/1005008159422892.html?aff_fcid=9f9d1107d9d3470d85d63865869692c2-1770810784580-04828-_c43YJPKT&amp;tt=CPS_NORMAL&amp;aff_fsk=_c43YJPKT&amp;aff_platform=portals-tool&amp;sk=_c43YJPKT&amp;aff_trace_key=9f9d1107d9d3470d85d63865869692c2-1770810784580-04828-_c43YJPKT&amp;terminal_id=1f7d0b4f2c174009b1f0c9cdc7092774&amp;afSmartRedirect=y#nav-description\" target=\"_blank\">ThinkRider’s XXPRO smart trainer</a> is also worth a quick mention because that trainer can generate its own energy by linking the direct drive with a generator. If you’ve got the power numbers of Tadej Pogačar, then do us all a favour and hook your trainer up to the National Grid.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from<a href=\"https://www.aliexpress.com/item/1005007715216416.html?aff_fcid=91f9289f44d14e2ba7e0b966f76272cb-1770810863672-09646-_c45eyn4P&amp;tt=CPS_NORMAL&amp;aff_fsk=_c45eyn4P&amp;aff_platform=portals-tool&amp;sk=_c45eyn4P&amp;aff_trace_key=91f9289f44d14e2ba7e0b966f76272cb-1770810863672-09646-_c45eyn4P&amp;terminal_id=1f7d0b4f2c174009b1f0c9cdc7092774&amp;afSmartRedirect=y#nav-specification\" target=\"_blank\"> AliExpress (from £250)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Muc-Off Foam Sprayer Kit</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-970x645.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-970x646.jpg 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-300x199.jpg 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-1536x1021.jpg 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-2048x1362.jpg 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-750x499.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-1140x758.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-465x310.jpg 465w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-620x413.jpg 620w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0117-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the depths of winter seem behind us, a clean bike is a year-round necessity. To help soften the blow of this post-ride chore, Muc-Off’s new Foam Sprayer offers an electric and hose-free tool to tidy up our mucky bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Foam Sprayer was developed in collaboration with IK Sprayers, a brand known for professional-grade sprayer technology. The sprayer works for both push-bikes and motorbikes and features chemical-resistant materials, a pressure release valve and an ergonomic handle.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s an analogue sprayer, there’s no electronics or hose required. All you need to do is combine the cleaning solution with water and pump away to create foam using the bottle top lever. After about 15 pumps, hold down the button atop the handle, and the foam will start to skoosh away. Note, there are two nozzle options, but the pink one is better suited to cleaning bikes, both frame and components.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-970x645.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-970x646.jpg 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-300x199.jpg 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-1536x1021.jpg 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-2048x1362.jpg 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-750x499.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-1140x758.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-465x310.jpg 465w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-620x413.jpg 620w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0120-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s ideal if you don’t have a garden or pipe to hand. All you need is some water and cleaning solution.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For £85, you can get the full sprayer kit. This includes 500ml of Muc-Off’s Cleaner Concentrate, a microfibre cloth, sponge and a set of three brushes. One of those is a technical brush to get into those difficult spots.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy the Foam Spray Kit now from <a href=\"https://muc-off.com/products/foam-sprayer-kit\" target=\"_blank\">Muc-Off (£85)</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Buy just the Foam Spray from <a href=\"https://muc-off.com/products/foam-sprayer\" target=\"_blank\">Muc-Off (£35)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>GripGrab FastStream aero gloves</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-970x645.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-970x646.jpg 970w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-300x199.jpg 300w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-1536x1021.jpg 1536w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-2048x1362.jpg 2048w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-750x499.jpg 750w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-1140x758.jpg 1140w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-465x310.jpg 465w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-620x413.jpg 620w, https://cdn-jupiter.metropolis.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/03/DSC_0199-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now the sun’s starting to come out, it’s time to ditch the layers and aero up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scandinavian brand GripGrab’s FastStream aero gloves are adapted from the brand’s time-trial gloves, with several watt-saving features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the palm, the padding has been removed and replaced with a perforated and recycled microsuede fabric around to improve breathability without sacrificing grip. For those aero bonuses, the stretchable fabric ensures your skin sits flush against the glove material to avoid any drag-inducing flaps around the front-end of the bike. Overall, this creates a bulk-free and streamlined fit that even the most glove-sceptic wouldn’t mind wearing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a seal of approval, these gloves have been modelled by WorldTour newcomers Uno X Mobility since the start of the year.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"http://gloves?srsltid=AfmBOoo28VSBCyRyIwCr6qtgRrsLafvOVqEOlhYjZEYOh2XCS9wVKzgT\" target=\"_blank\">GripGrab (£45)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: James Blake</h2>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>James Blake has been kicking around for some time, having broken through during the 2010s, and he’s had popular collaborations with a mix of R&amp;B and rap artists as well as Catalan songstress Rosalía.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This morning, Blake dropped his latest album <em>Trying Times</em>. The 13-track record covers a breadth of genres, with sounds both nostalgic and current. My favourite is ‘Make Something Up’, but there’s something for everyone on this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>James Blake is hardly underground, so expect to hear his name pop up in the following weeks as listeners chew through the album. Plus, he’s scheduled to do the festival rounds this summer as he gears up for a US and European Tour in the autumn. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/thinkrider-x2max-smart-trainer\">In The Drops: ThinkRider X2Max Smart Trainer, Muc-Off Foam Sprayer, GripGrab FastStream gloves and James Blake</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Ewan Wilson &#124; Staff Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"84f274cd431ce67e078dd444a25823a229f308c90681c1b1f364fb1599d79cdf","category":"Cycling"}